---
import Layout from "../layouts/as.astro";
import "../styles/gear/gear.css";
---

<Layout title="Our Gear">
    <div class="equipment-content">
        <div class="upperBg">
            <div class="upperFader">
                <p class="top-title">
                    Discover the gear that brings FlyFree to life
                </p>
                <h1 class="equipment-title">Our Camera Gear</h1>

                <div class="our-vision">
                    <p>
                        "Reliable and mobile gear that captures nature's quiet
                        moments and boldest movements wherever the wild leads"
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panels gear-current">
            <h2>Our Current Camera Rig</h2>

            <div class="current-para-wrapper">
                <div class="current-para-wrapper-item">
                    <p class="main-para current-para">
                        Built for the ever-changing conditions of the wild, it
                        lets us move freely, adapt quickly, and stay focused on
                        the story unfolding in front of us. Every part of this
                        setup is chosen to keep us steady, responsive, and ready
                        to capture those fleeting natural moments that matter
                        most.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="imageWrapper">
                    <img
                        src="/images/gear/current-rig.webp"
                        alt="current rig"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panels gear-main-cam">
            <h2>Our Main Workhorse</h2>
            <div class="para-item">
                <h3>Sony FX30 - <span>where every frame begins.</span></h3>
                <p class="main-para">
                    The Sony FX30 is at the heart of everything we capture. It’s
                    compact, reliable, and delivers beautiful 4K footage at 120
                    frames per second. Whether we're filming graceful bird
                    movements or calm morning reflections, this camera helps us
                    bring moments to life. <br /><br />Its low-light performance
                    and smooth slow-motion capabilities make it ideal for
                    working in nature, where light changes quickly and nothing
                    waits. From handheld shots in muddy terrain to tripod setups
                    by the lagoon, this is the tool we trust the most.
                </p>
                <img
                    src="/images/gear/fx30.webp"
                    alt="camera"
                    class="singleImage"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panel-full-bg">
            <div class="gear-panels gear-lenses">
                <h2>Eyes for the Wild</h2>

                <div class="para-item para-items-lens">
                    <div class="lens-para-wrapper">
                        <div class="lens-para-wrapper-item">
                            <h3>
                                Sony FE 200-600mm f/5.6-6.3 G OSS <span
                                    >for flexible reach in the wild.</span
                                >
                            </h3>
                            <p class="main-para lens-para">
                                Our go-to telephoto lens for wildlife. It offers
                                excellent reach and reliable sharpness, even at
                                long distances. Fast autofocus helps us track
                                birds in motion while staying far enough to
                                observe natural behavior without interruption.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="imageWrapper">
                            <img
                                src="/images/gear/600tele.webp"
                                alt="600m lens"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="para-item para-items-lens">
                    <div class="lens-para-wrapper">
                        <div class="lens-para-wrapper-item">
                            <h3>
                                Sony FE 24-105mm f/4 G OSS <span
                                    >for the wider story around us.</span
                                >
                            </h3>
                            <p class="main-para lens-para">
                                A versatile and lightweight zoom lens that helps
                                us capture landscapes, behind-the-scenes scenes,
                                and habitat context. It's sharp, stable, and
                                always ready when the moment calls for something
                                broader.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="imageWrapper">
                            <img src="/images/gear/24mm.webp" alt="24mm lens" />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panels gear-drones">
            <h2>Wings in the Sky</h2>

            <div class="para-item">
                <h3>
                    DJI Air 2S <span
                        >for agile flights and cinematic skies.</span
                    >
                </h3>
                <p class="main-para">
                    The DJI Air 2S is our go-to eye in the sky. With its 1-inch
                    sensor and crisp 5.4K video, it captures breathtaking aerial
                    perspectives that bring scale and depth to our stories. <br
                    /><br />
                    Lightweight and quick to deploy, it's perfect for spontaneous
                    sunrise launches or low sweeps above water. Its compact build
                    doesn't compromise on image quality. Whether flying over lagoons,
                    treetops, or tracking birds in motion, this drone keeps our vision
                    sharp and steady.
                </p>
                <img
                    src="/images/gear/drone.webp"
                    alt="camera"
                    class="singleImage"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panel-full-bg">
            <div class="gear-panels gear-support">
                <h2>Stability on the Move</h2>

                <div class="para-item para-items-support">
                    <div class="support-para-wrapper">
                        <div class="support-para-wrapper-item">
                            <h3>
                                DJI RS 4 <span
                                    >for smooth motion and creative control.</span
                                >
                            </h3>
                            <p class="main-para support-para">
                                The DJI RS 4 is our trusted gimbal for capturing
                                fluid motion shots, even when we're on the move.
                                It balances the Sony FX30 effortlessly and opens
                                up dynamic angles while maintaining steady
                                footage. Whether walking through rough terrain
                                or circling a subject, it gives us freedom to
                                move while keeping the visuals rock-solid and
                                cinematic.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="imageWrapper">
                            <img
                                src="/images/gear/rs4.png"
                                alt="DJI RS 4 Gimbal"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="para-item para-items-support">
                    <div class="support-para-wrapper">
                        <div class="support-para-wrapper-item">
                            <h3>
                                Sirui SH25 Tripod <span
                                    >our solid ground support.</span
                                >
                            </h3>
                            <p class="main-para support-para">
                                The Sirui SH25 tripod is our stable base for
                                capturing wide landscapes, interviews, or slow
                                pans across nature. Its fluid head ensures
                                smooth camera movements, while the aluminum legs
                                keep everything sturdy, even in uneven or muddy
                                environments. Quick to set up and strong enough
                                to hold heavier gear, it's a vital part of our
                                grounded shots.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="imageWrapper">
                            <img
                                src="/images/gear/sh25.png"
                                alt="Sirui SH25 Tripod"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panels gear-software">
            <h2>Where the Story Comes Alive</h2>

            <div class="para-item">
                <h3>DaVinci Resolve - <span>From Raw to Remarkable</span></h3>
                <p class="main-para">
                    DaVinci Resolve is where our stories truly take shape. From
                    gentle color tones to dramatic contrasts, it helps us craft
                    the mood behind each scene. Whether it's revealing the
                    golden light over the lagoon or fine-tuning the rhythm of
                    birds in flight, this software is essential for bringing
                    emotion and flow to our wildlife films.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="para-item">
                <h3>Photoshop - <span>for moments frozen in time.</span></h3>
                <p class="main-para">
                    Photoshop lets us relive our favorite moments through
                    stills. From crisp bird portraits to dramatic landscapes, we
                    use it to enhance every detail while preserving the raw
                    beauty of nature. It's a key part of our process — helping
                    us prepare thumbnails, posters, and standout images that
                    tell their own silent stories.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="gear-panel-full-bg">
            <div class="gear-panels gear-extra">
                <h2>The Gear Behind the Gear</h2>
                <p class="main-para">
                    These are the unsung heroes that keep our setups running
                    smoothly in the wild — supporting, powering, and stabilizing
                    every shot.
                </p>

                <ul class="gear-list">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Sony FE 1.4x Teleconverter</strong><br />
                        Extends our reach for distant wildlife while maintaining
                        sharpness and autofocus reliability.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>K&F Concept 99Wh V-Mount Battery</strong><br />
                        Provides extended power in the field — no outlets, no problem.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            >Sirui Full Camera Cage Kit for Sony FX3 & FX30</strong
                        ><br />
                        Adds protection and mounting flexibility for monitors, handles,
                        and accessories.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Eirmai TR629 25L Camera Backpack</strong><br />
                        Carries it all — safely and comfortably across rugged terrains.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            >FeelWorld LUT7 PRO 7" Ultrabright HDMI Field
                            Monitor</strong
                        ><br />
                        Lets us see our shots clearly in harsh sunlight and mount
                        accessories with ease.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>SmallRig Camera Base Plate with Rod Rail</strong
                        ><br />
                        Forms the foundation of our rig, ensuring secure mounting
                        and modularity.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            >SmallRig 2PCS 15mm Carbon Fiber Rod (30CM)</strong
                        ><br />
                        Lightweight yet strong — supports all the accessories in
                        the rig.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>SmallRig Universal Lens Support</strong><br />
                        Adds stability to heavy lenses and reduces strain on the
                        camera mount.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>RM-VPR1 Remote Shutter Release Cable</strong><br
                        />
                        Enables shake-free captures from a distance during precise
                        moments.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

